    "body": "https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/4459 introduces filtering of peers in the discovery layerin besu. Benefits are a reduced number of connection attempts on the Rlpx layer, and connections that are attempted have a better chance to result in a useful connection to a peer on the higher layers.\r\nAll major clients, except for Nethermind, send the fork id as part of the ENR response.  If Nethermind were to send it the number of unnecessary connection attempts would be even smaller.",
